Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: thermal bridge simulation software (EN 10211)
 conducteo is a software package for numerical simulation of linear thermal bridges
 according to EN 10211.
 .
 It provides detailed thermal analysis of building components, including heat
 flow calculations, temperature fields, thermal bridge coefficients (ψ-values),
 U-values, and equivalent thermal conductivity.
 .
 Features include:
  - 2D steady-state thermal simulation
  - Computes heat flows, ψ-values, U-values, and equivalent thermal conductivity
  - Support for distributed thermal bridges by thermal environment
  - Condensation risk analysis using the Glaser method
  - Imports THERM models
  - Imports DXF files for geometry
  - Exports calculation reports (PDF and DocX)
 .
 The documentation and materials database are currently mainly available in
 French, which may limit usability for non-French-speaking users.